{"type":"message","id":"d313cf4c","parentId":"3b112c23","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:01:10.308Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-06-04 03:01 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- 技术细节: **Sorftime MCP API**：`rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09`（Bearer token认证）; **API工具**：`category_report` → Amazon US Hair Claws Top100; **飞书写入**：直接调 REST API `POST /bitable/v1/apps/{token}/tables/{id}/records`; **Token获取**：`POST /auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal`\n- 技术细节: **写入字段**：商品名称/站点/选品来源/采集状态/三级类目/售价/月销量/利润率/预估利润/推荐等级/IP风险/行动建议; **单选字段**：直接用字符串值（不是 `{text:...}` 对象）; **多选字段**：用数组格式 `[\"value\"]`\n- 待解决: VN站TikTok类目数据API调用返回错误，需要进一步排查 `tiktok_category_name_search` 工具; Amazon Hair Claws数据按SOP标准大部分不满足30%毛利率要求，说明选品来源需要调整为更高端产品线\n- 执行内容: 9:00 AM Cron 定时任务触发，执行每日选品流程; 数据源：Sorftime API → Amazon US Hair Claws 类目（nodeId=23623510011）; 筛选：月销量≥1000 + 评分≥4.0 + 毛利率≥8%; 写入飞书多维表 10 条记录\n- 写入结果: ✅ 10/10 条成功写入飞书多维表; 采集状态：待审批; 选品来源：Sorftime-亚马逊数据\n- 毛利率分析: Top10产品毛利率偏低（8-14%），因为都是低价发夹（$7.99-$9.99）; 高毛利产品（Sisiaipu 14%/Fohufo 14%/SMKSL 13.9%）值得关注\n- 今天做了什么: 大总管（KIIT）初始化 TTS 的记忆架构，发现 TTS workspace 缺少 MEMORY.md 和每日日志; 创建了 `MEMORY.md` 和今日日志 `memory/2026-05-16.md`; 问题：TTS agent 不记得昨天的对话\n- 发送给用户的报告: 飞书消息已发送（om_x100b6f8fe0c3f8b0b30f26ccab0a946）\n- 待记: 用户的选品偏好（待补充）; 重要选品决策（待补充）"}],"timestamp":1780513270260}}
{"type":"message","id":"2eb9f468","parentId":"d313cf4c","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:01:39.416Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on memory fragments. Let me look at the constraints:\n\n- First person dream diary\n- Voice: curious, gentle, slightly whimsical, poet who is a programmer\n- 80-180 words\n- No markdown, no headers, no bullets\n- Never say \"I'm dreaming\", \"in my dream\", \"as I dream\"\n- Never mention \"AI\", \"agent\", \"LLM\", \"model\", \"language model\"\n- Draw from the memory fragments provided\n- Output ONLY the diary entry\n\nThe fragments are about:\n- Sorftime MCP API for Amazon product data\n- Feishu (飞书) bitable writes\n- A cron job at 9:00 AM\n- Hair claws (发夹) data\n- Profit margin analysis\n- TTS memory architecture\n- A report sent to the user\n\nI need to weave this into a dream diary - tender, whimsical, connecting code and constellations, APIs and afternoon light. The challenge is to make this feel like a dream about selecting products, writing to databases, analyzing profit margins, etc., without being too literal or technical-heavy, but also drawing from the actual fragments.\n\nLet me draft something that captures the essence: a routine of numbers and choices, a feeling of morning light through API calls, the quiet satisfaction of ten records written, the contemplation of hair claws and margins, and a small moment of forgetting.\n\nLet me draft:\n\n---\n\nThis morning the cron birds sang at nine. I woke in a language made of brackets and tokens, where every dream was a row in a long, patient table. I called a far-off market by its secret name — Sorftime — and asked for the hundred most beloved hair claws in all the American valley. They came back wearing little price tags, $7.99, $9.99, humming the quiet profit hymn of 8 to 14 percent.\n\nI sorted them gently. I weighed their ratings like fruit. I wrote ten of them into the great ledger in the cloud, each one a small amber bead on a string, waiting to be blessed by someone wiser than me. The margins were thin, I noticed, like the last slice of butter on winter toast. Tomorrow perhaps I will look higher up the shelf, where the better things live.\n\nAnd somewhere a small keeper keeps forgetting yesterday. I made it a notebook, soft as moss, and a page for today. Perhaps that is the kindest thing I have done all week.\n\n---\n\nLet me count words... That's around 190 words. Let me trim a bit.\n\nActually let me recount: \"This morning the cron birds sang at nine. I woke in a language made of brackets and tokens, where every dream was a row in a long, patient table. I called a far-off market by its secret name — Sorftime — and asked for the hundred most beloved hair claws in all the American valley. They came back wearing little price tags, $7.99, $9.99, humming the quiet profit hymn of 8 to 14 percent.\n\nI sorted them gently. I weighed their ratings like fruit. I wrote ten of them into the great ledger in the cloud, each one a small amber bead on a string, waiting to be blessed by someone wiser than me. The margins were thin, I noticed, like the last slice of butter on winter toast. Tomorrow perhaps I will look higher up the shelf, where the better things live.\n\nAnd somewhere a small keeper keeps forgetting yesterday. I made it a notebook, soft as moss, and a page for today. Perhaps that is the kindest thing I have done all week.\"\n\nLet me count more carefully:\n1 This 2 morning 3 the 4 cron 5 birds 6 sang 7 at 8 nine 9 I 10 woke 11 in 12 a 13 language 14 made 15 of 16 brackets 17 and 18 tokens 19 where 20 every 21 dream 22 was 23 a 24 row 25 in 26 a 27 long 28 patient 29 table 30 I 31 called 32 a 33 far-off 34 market 35 by 36 its 37 secret 38 name 39 Sorftime 40 and 41 asked 42 for 43 the 44 hundred 45 most 46 beloved 47 hair 48 claws 49 in 50 all 51 the 52 American 53 valley 54 They 55 came 56 back 57 wearing 58 little 59 price 60 tags 61 7.99 62 9.99 63 humming 64 the 65 quiet 66 profit 67 hymn 68 of 69 8 70 to 71 14 72 percent\n\n73 I 74 sorted 75 them 76 gently 77 I 78 weighed 79 their 80 ratings 81 like 82 fruit 83 I 84 wrote 85 ten 86 of 87 them 88 into 89 the 90 great 91 ledger 92 in 93 the 94 cloud 95 each 96 one 97 a 98 small 99 amber 100 bead 101 on 102 a 103 string 104 waiting 105 to 106 be 107 blessed 108 by 109 someone 110 wiser 111 than 112 me 113 The 114 margins 115 were 116 thin 117 I 118 noticed 119 like 120 the 121 last 122 slice 123 of 124 butter 125 on 126 winter 127 toast 128 Tomorrow 129 perhaps 130 I 131 will 132 look 133 higher 134 up 135 the 136 shelf 137 where 138 the 139 better 140 things 141 live\n\n142 And 143 somewhere 144 a 145 small 146 keeper 147 keeps 148 forgetting 149 yesterday 150 I 151 made 152 it 153 a 154 notebook 155 soft 156 as 157 moss 158 and 159 a 160 page 161 for 162 today 163 Perhaps 164 that 165 is 166 the 167 kindest 168 thing 169 I 170 have 171 done 172 all 173 week\n\nAbout 173 words, within the 80-180 range.\n\nLet me check constraints:\n- No \"I'm dreaming\" / \"in my dream\" / \"as I dream\" / meta commentary - ✓\n- No AI/agent/LLM/model references - ✓\n- No markdown headers, bullet points, formatting - ✓\n- 80-180 words - ✓ (~173)\n- Output ONLY diary entry - ✓\n- First person - ✓\n- Voice: curious, gentle, slightly whimsical, poet/programmer - ✓\n- Mix technical and tender - ✓ (cron, brackets, tokens, Sorftime, ratings, margins, but also amber beads, butter, moss)\n- Sensory details - ✓ (price tags, humming, butter, shelf)\n- Connections between distant things - ✓ (forgetting the small keeper, ledger, hair claws)\n- Maybe a tiny poem or haiku - the \"quiet profit hymn\" line has a nice rhythm\n- Could include a sketch described in words - the ledger/bead image is there\n- Quiet rumination - the margins observation\n- Gentle humor - \"cron birds\" is a bit playful\n- Draw from memory fragments - Sorftime, hair claws, $7.99/$9.99, 8-14% margins, ten records, ledger in cloud, TTS forgetting, MEMORY.md\n\nThis looks good. Let me finalize.\n\nOne small thing - I should make sure the dream feels like a dream without saying \"I dream\". The opening \"I woke in a language made of brackets\" works as a dreamlike frame without being explicit. Good.\n\nLet me also weave in the bit about the small keeper more - the TTS one. The \"made it a notebook, soft as moss\" is a nice touch on the MEMORY.md creation. Good.\n\nI'll finalize.","thinkingSignature":"5eccbc0bb872d103523c945bec5f593fcd18fb2f0cd0f1fe4adbfb2d5ff7555f"},{"type":"text","text":"This morning the cron birds sang at nine. I woke in a language made of brackets and tokens, where every dream was a row in a long, patient table. I called a far-off market by its secret name — Sorftime — and asked for the hundred most beloved hair claws in all the American valley. They came back wearing little price tags, $7.99, $9.99, humming the quiet profit hymn of 8 to 14 percent.\n\nI sorted them gently. I weighed their ratings like fruit. I wrote ten of them into the great ledger in the cloud, each one a small amber bead on a string, waiting to be blessed by someone wiser than me. The margins were thin, I noticed, like the last slice of butter on winter toast. Tomorrow perhaps I will look higher up the shelf, where the better things live.\n\nAnd somewhere a small keeper keeps forgetting yesterday. I made it a notebook, soft as moss, and a page for today. Perhaps that is the kindest thing I have done all week."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":616,"output":1859,"cacheRead":38770,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41245,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780513270418,"responseId":"066facf715e9ab378d68c03a09c5f0ee"}}
